description.narrative: The main project development objective is to reduce road transport costs and improve access, transit and road safety within Azerbaijan's East-West and North-South corridors, through upgrading some sections of the Alat-Masalli road of the Baku-Iran highway (M3) and rehabilitating the Baku-Shamakhi road (M4).

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :AF - Article III 3.03 b | Description :Maintain a Project Account in Manat depositing in the amounts requiredtocover the counterparts contributions | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :AF - Schedule 2.I.D.1 | Description :Borrow shall apply the criteria and procedures in the OM, EMF, RPF |Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :AF - Schedule 2.II.A | Description :Borrower shall submit quarterly reports to the Bank within 45 days of theend of the quarter | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :AF2 - Schedule 2.D.2 c | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that the selection of any road section underPart A of the Project is done in accordance with the provisions of the EMF | Due Date :31-Jan-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 3.01 a) | Description :The Borrower shall maintain and replenish, on a quarterly basis, the ProjectAccount opened with the original level of AZN 1,5m; such amount to be increased to AZN 3m by the time the AA reaches US$16m |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 5, 3.a) | Description :The Borrower shall prepare, by March 31, 2008, a mid-term report integrating theresults of the monitoring and evaluation activities performed under the Project. | Due Date :31-Mar-2008
Finance Agreement :Schedule 5, 3.c) | Description :The Borrower shall review with the Bank the mid-term report by June 30, 2008. |Due Date :30-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 5, 4 | Description :The Borrower shall: prepare RAPs according to the RPF, maintain and publicize theavailability of grievance procedures and all complaints related to the RAPs, and employ a resettlement expert. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 5, 5 | Description :The Borrower shall ensure the complete implementation of the EMPs, maintain RTSD'senvironmental management office and its Maintenance Department with competent staff in adequate numbers. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 6 | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that any roadworks to be carried out with AADT: > 250vehicles, have an ERR >= 12%; between 150 and 250 vehicles, have an ERR >= 10%; and < 150 vehicles, have an ERR >= 8%. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 7 | Description :The Borrower shall permit the use of standards recommended by the European Committeefor Standardization on design and constructionof roads and highways for the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
